  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nWhen adding an extension that contains `cli-plugins` as part of its metadta, then the defined plugins should be automatically added to the CLI (when inside the project).\r\n\r\nThis works if another plugin has been already added to the project ( <project root>/.quarkus/cli/plugins/quarkus-cli-catalog.json exists). But it doesn't if it is not.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nAfter adding `quarkus-helm` the `quarkus --help` should include the `helm` cli.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nThe `helm` cli does not appear, unless we manually run `quarkus plug sync`.\n\n### How to Reproduce?\n\nReproducer \r\n1. quarkus create app reproducer\r\n2. cd reproducer\r\n3. git init\r\n4. quarkus ext add quarkus-helm\r\n5. quarkus --help\r\n\r\n*Note*: The git init is added to ensure that the plugin mechanism won't look higher in the dir hierarchy which could yield inconsistent results.\r\n\n\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\n\n_No response_\n\n### Output of `java -version`\n\n_No response_\n\n### GraalVM version (if different from Java)\n\n_No response_\n\n### Quarkus version or git rev\n\n_No response_\n\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional information\n\n_No response_",
